        ],
        [
          "Clustering",
          "Higher Education",
          "B-Learning",
          "114 undergraduate students",
          "1 Course in a Bachelor's program in Economic and  Business Education at an European University",
          "LMS logs, Self Assessment Results, Questionnaires",
          "None Specified",
          "[Ratio of last self-assessment  attempt against best self-assessment possible, ratio of processeed tasks of each self-assessment, attempts per self-assessment, procesing time per self-assessment]",
          "Data was cleaned from the LMS during self-assessments (11 in total) - 44 features in total.\n\nAll were standardized. ",
          "k-Means",
          "2 Clusters were selected based on WCSS and Sillhouette Score",
          "2",
          "High engagement (n=51): higher engasgement with self-assessments throughout the semester\n\nlow-engagement (n=107): lower engagement throughout the semesters.\n\nBoth groups have similar engagement for the mid-term test.",
          "Students seem to use self-assessment at specific moments in a semester AND studdents who are more engaged seem to obtain better performance than their peers. \n\nLearning analytics dashboards should not only draw relationship between engagement and performance and instead should provide process-oriented feedback. ",
          "Authors use k-means on a set of students and then check whether there is agreement between the observed data for engagement against:\n\n1. Overall engagement with resources - there is.\n\n2. Alignment with Self-Reported data - there is as well. ",
          "Single course.\n\nLimited number of self-reported variables weere cconsidered. \n\nSelf-Assessments were limited to specific lessons and not framed in a hollistic manner.\n\nNo analysis of learner progression.\n\n"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 5
    }
  ],
